metadata.name: The Abominable Ocean
metadata.description:
“If the others heard me talking out loud they would think that I am crazy. But since I am not crazy, I do not care.”

(Ernest Hemmingway, The Old Man and the Sea)

Every day he waits, he waits, he waits  
The lick of the tide, the sluice 
By the ocean, the ceaseless ocean  
A recklessness of abominable water...
